      • handleBulkMiss

        void handleBulkMiss(java.util.HashMap<K,V> retrievedObjects,
                  K[] keys)
        handleBulkMiss retrieves multiple objects in a single pass. Keys are passed in in the keys array. The retrieved objects are inserted into the retrievedObjects HashMap that is passed in. Keys that are null will leave the corresponding entry in the retrievedObjects HashMap in whatever state it was when passed in. This allows the cache to find all cached objects and then just ask for the ones it needs

        retrievedObjects -
